    <item>
      <title>Guides: Overview: rad CLI</title>
      <link>https://docs.radapp.io/guides/tooling/rad-cli/overview/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://docs.radapp.io/guides/tooling/rad-cli/overview/</guid>
      <description>
        
        
        &lt;p&gt;The rad Command Line Interface (CLI) allows you to interact with Radius from your local machine. It is the primary way to interact with Radius and is used to create, deploy, and manage your applications, environments, and resources.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;$ rad
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Radius CLI
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Usage:
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;  rad &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;command&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Available Commands:
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;  application Manage Radius Applications
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;  bicep       Manage bicep compiler
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;  completion  Generates shell completion scripts
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;  credential  Manage cloud provider credential &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; a Radius installation.
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;  debug-logs  Capture logs from Radius control plane &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; debugging and diagnostics.
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;  deploy      Deploy a template
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;  env         Manage Radius Environments
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;  group       Manage resource groups
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;  help        Help about any command
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;  init        Initialize Radius
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;  install     Installs Radius &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; a given platform
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;  recipe      Manage recipes
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;  resource    Manage resources
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;  run         Run an application
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;  uninstall   Uninstall Radius &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; a specific platform
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;  version     Prints the versions of the rad cli
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;  workspace   Manage workspaces
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;installation&#34;&gt;Installation&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The rad CLI is distributed as a single binary that can be installed on Linux, macOS, and Windows. Visit the &lt;a href=&#34;https://docs.radapp.io/guides/tooling/rad-cli/howto-rad-cli/&#34;&gt;installation guide&lt;/a&gt; to learn how to install the rad CLI.&lt;/p&gt;









&lt;a class=&#34;btn  btn-primary&#34; href=&#34;https://docs.radapp.io/guides/tooling/rad-cli/howto-rad-cli/&#34; role=&#34;button&#34;&gt;Install rad CLI&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;binary-location&#34;&gt;Binary location&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul class=&#34;nav nav-tabs&#34; id=&#34;tabs-2&#34; role=&#34;tablist&#34;&gt;&lt;li class=&#34;nav-item&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;nav-link active&#34;
    id=&#34;tabs-2-macoslinuxwsl-tab&#34; data-toggle=&#34;tab&#34; href=&#34;#tabs-2-macoslinuxwsl&#34; role=&#34;tab&#34;
    aria-controls=&#34;tabs-2-macoslinuxwsl&#34; aria-selected=&#34;true&#34;&gt;
    macOS/Linux/WSL
  &lt;/a&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class=&#34;nav-item&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;nav-link&#34;
    id=&#34;tabs-2-windows-tab&#34; data-toggle=&#34;tab&#34; href=&#34;#tabs-2-windows&#34; role=&#34;tab&#34;
    aria-controls=&#34;tabs-2-windows&#34; aria-selected=&#34;false&#34;&gt;
    Windows
  &lt;/a&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;div class=&#34;tab-content&#34; id=&#34;tabs-2-content&#34;&gt;


&lt;div class=&#34;tab-pane fade show active&#34; id=&#34;tabs-2-macoslinuxwsl&#34; role=&#34;tabpanel&#34; aria-labelled-by=&#34;tabs-2-macoslinuxwsl-tab&#34;&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;p&gt;By default, the rad CLI installation script installs the rad CLI to &lt;code&gt;/usr/local/bin/rad&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like to install the rad CLI to a different path, you can specify the path with the &lt;code&gt;RADIUS_INSTALL_DIR&lt;/code&gt; environment variable:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#75715e&#34;&gt;# Install to home directory&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;export RADIUS_INSTALL_DIR&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;~/
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&#34;tab-pane fade&#34; id=&#34;tabs-2-windows&#34; role=&#34;tabpanel&#34; aria-labelled-by=&#34;tabs-2-windows-tab&#34;&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;p&gt;By default, the rad CLI installation script installs the rad CLI to &lt;code&gt;%LOCALAPPDATA%\radius\rad.exe&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
    

&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;configuration-location&#34;&gt;Configuration location&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The rad CLI stores workspaces, the rad-Bicep compiler, and other configuration under the &lt;code&gt;rad&lt;/code&gt; directory.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&#34;nav nav-tabs&#34; id=&#34;tabs-3&#34; role=&#34;tablist&#34;&gt;&lt;li class=&#34;nav-item&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;nav-link active&#34;
    id=&#34;tabs-3-macoslinuxwsl-tab&#34; data-toggle=&#34;tab&#34; href=&#34;#tabs-3-macoslinuxwsl&#34; role=&#34;tab&#34;
    aria-controls=&#34;tabs-3-macoslinuxwsl&#34; aria-selected=&#34;true&#34;&gt;
    macOS/Linux/WSL
  &lt;/a&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class=&#34;nav-item&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;nav-link&#34;
    id=&#34;tabs-3-windows-tab&#34; data-toggle=&#34;tab&#34; href=&#34;#tabs-3-windows&#34; role=&#34;tab&#34;
    aria-controls=&#34;tabs-3-windows&#34; aria-selected=&#34;false&#34;&gt;
    Windows
  &lt;/a&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;div class=&#34;tab-content&#34; id=&#34;tabs-3-content&#34;&gt;


&lt;div class=&#34;tab-pane fade show active&#34; id=&#34;tabs-3-macoslinuxwsl&#34; role=&#34;tabpanel&#34; aria-labelled-by=&#34;tabs-3-macoslinuxwsl-tab&#34;&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;p&gt;The rad CLI stores configuration under &lt;code&gt;~/.rad&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&#34;tab-pane fade&#34; id=&#34;tabs-3-windows&#34; role=&#34;tabpanel&#34; aria-labelled-by=&#34;tabs-3-windows-tab&#34;&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;p&gt;The rad CLI stores configuration under &lt;code&gt;%USERPROFILE%\rad&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
    

&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;reference-documentation&#34;&gt;Reference documentation&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Visit the &lt;a href=&#34;https://docs.radapp.io/reference/cli/&#34;&gt;reference documentation&lt;/a&gt; to learn more about the rad CLI and its commands.&lt;/p&gt;









&lt;a class=&#34;btn  btn-primary&#34; href=&#34;https://docs.radapp.io/reference/cli/&#34; role=&#34;button&#34;&gt;Reference docs&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;

      </description>
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Guides: How-To: Install the rad CLI</title>
      <link>https://docs.radapp.io/guides/tooling/rad-cli/howto-rad-cli/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://docs.radapp.io/guides/tooling/rad-cli/howto-rad-cli/</guid>
      <description>
        
        
        

&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;rad&lt;/code&gt; CLI manages your applications, resources, and environments. You can install it on your local machine with the following installation scripts:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&#34;nav nav-tabs&#34; id=&#34;tabs-0&#34; role=&#34;tablist&#34;&gt;&lt;li class=&#34;nav-item&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;nav-link active&#34;
    id=&#34;tabs-0-linuxwsl-tab&#34; data-toggle=&#34;tab&#34; href=&#34;#tabs-0-linuxwsl&#34; role=&#34;tab&#34;
    aria-controls=&#34;tabs-0-linuxwsl&#34; aria-selected=&#34;true&#34;&gt;
    Linux/WSL
  &lt;/a&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class=&#34;nav-item&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;nav-link&#34;
    id=&#34;tabs-0-macos-tab&#34; data-toggle=&#34;tab&#34; href=&#34;#tabs-0-macos&#34; role=&#34;tab&#34;
    aria-controls=&#34;tabs-0-macos&#34; aria-selected=&#34;false&#34;&gt;
    MacOS
  &lt;/a&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class=&#34;nav-item&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;nav-link&#34;
    id=&#34;tabs-0-windows-powershell-tab&#34; data-toggle=&#34;tab&#34; href=&#34;#tabs-0-windows-powershell&#34; role=&#34;tab&#34;
    aria-controls=&#34;tabs-0-windows-powershell&#34; aria-selected=&#34;false&#34;&gt;
    Windows PowerShell
  &lt;/a&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class=&#34;nav-item&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;nav-link&#34;
    id=&#34;tabs-0-github-codespace-tab&#34; data-toggle=&#34;tab&#34; href=&#34;#tabs-0-github-codespace&#34; role=&#34;tab&#34;
    aria-controls=&#34;tabs-0-github-codespace&#34; aria-selected=&#34;false&#34;&gt;
    GitHub Codespace
  &lt;/a&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class=&#34;nav-item&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;nav-link&#34;
    id=&#34;tabs-0-azure-cloud-shell-tab&#34; data-toggle=&#34;tab&#34; href=&#34;#tabs-0-azure-cloud-shell&#34; role=&#34;tab&#34;
    aria-controls=&#34;tabs-0-azure-cloud-shell&#34; aria-selected=&#34;false&#34;&gt;
    Azure Cloud Shell
  &lt;/a&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class=&#34;nav-item&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;nav-link&#34;
    id=&#34;tabs-0-binaries-tab&#34; data-toggle=&#34;tab&#34; href=&#34;#tabs-0-binaries&#34; role=&#34;tab&#34;
    aria-controls=&#34;tabs-0-binaries&#34; aria-selected=&#34;false&#34;&gt;
    Binaries
  &lt;/a&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;div class=&#34;tab-content&#34; id=&#34;tabs-0-content&#34;&gt;


&lt;div class=&#34;tab-pane fade show active&#34; id=&#34;tabs-0-linuxwsl&#34; role=&#34;tabpanel&#34; aria-labelled-by=&#34;tabs-0-linuxwsl-tab&#34;&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;wget -q &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;https://raw.githubusercontent.com/radius-project/radius/main/deploy/install.sh&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; -O - | /bin/bash
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;To try out an unstable release visit the &lt;a href=&#34;https://edge.docs.radapp.io&#34;&gt;edge docs&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&#34;tab-pane fade&#34; id=&#34;tabs-0-macos&#34; role=&#34;tabpanel&#34; aria-labelled-by=&#34;tabs-0-macos-tab&#34;&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;curl -fsSL &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;https://raw.githubusercontent.com/radius-project/radius/main/deploy/install.sh&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; | /bin/bash
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;To try out an unstable release visit the &lt;a href=&#34;https://edge.docs.radapp.io&#34;&gt;edge docs&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&#34;tab-pane fade&#34; id=&#34;tabs-0-windows-powershell&#34; role=&#34;tabpanel&#34; aria-labelled-by=&#34;tabs-0-windows-powershell-tab&#34;&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;p&gt;Run the following in a PowerShell window:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-powershell&#34; data-lang=&#34;powershell&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;iwr -useb &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;https://raw.githubusercontent.com/radius-project/radius/main/deploy/install.ps1&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; | iex
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;You may need to refresh your $PATH environment variable to access &lt;code&gt;rad&lt;/code&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-powershell&#34; data-lang=&#34;powershell&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;$Env:Path = [&lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;System.Environment&lt;/span&gt;]::GetEnvironmentVariable(&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Path&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;,&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;User&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;To try out an unstable release visit the &lt;a href=&#34;https://edge.docs.radapp.io&#34;&gt;edge docs&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&#34;tab-pane fade&#34; id=&#34;tabs-0-github-codespace&#34; role=&#34;tabpanel&#34; aria-labelled-by=&#34;tabs-0-github-codespace-tab&#34;&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;p&gt;Radius offers a &lt;strong&gt;free&lt;/strong&gt; Codespace option for getting up and running with a Radius environment in seconds:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://codespaces.new/radius-project/samples&#34;&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://github.com/codespaces/badge.svg&#34; alt=&#34;Open in GitHub Codespaces&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&#34;tab-pane fade&#34; id=&#34;tabs-0-azure-cloud-shell&#34; role=&#34;tabpanel&#34; aria-labelled-by=&#34;tabs-0-azure-cloud-shell-tab&#34;&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/cloud-shell/overview&#34;&gt;Azure Cloud Shell&lt;/a&gt; is an interactive, authenticated, browser-accessible shell for managing Azure resources.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Azure Cloud Shell for bash doesn&amp;rsquo;t have a sudo command, so users are unable to install Radius to the default &lt;code&gt;/usr/local/bin&lt;/code&gt; installation path. To install the rad CLI to the home directory, run the following commands:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;export RADIUS_INSTALL_DIR&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;./
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;wget -q &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;https://raw.githubusercontent.com/radius-project/radius/main/deploy/install.sh&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; -O - | /bin/bash
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;You can now run the rad CLI with &lt;code&gt;./rad&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;PowerShell for Cloud Shell is currently not supported.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&#34;tab-pane fade&#34; id=&#34;tabs-0-binaries&#34; role=&#34;tabpanel&#34; aria-labelled-by=&#34;tabs-0-binaries-tab&#34;&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;p&gt;Visit &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/radius-project/radius/releases&#34;&gt;Radius GitHub releases&lt;/a&gt; to select and download a specific version of the rad CLI.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You may be prompted for your sudo password during installation, as the installer places the &lt;code&gt;rad&lt;/code&gt; binary under &lt;code&gt;/usr/local/bin&lt;/code&gt;. If you are unable to sudo you can install the rad CLI to another directory by setting the &lt;code&gt;RADIUS_INSTALL_DIR&lt;/code&gt; environment variable with your intended install path. Make sure you add this to your path (&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.howtogeek.com/658904/how-to-add-a-directory-to-your-path-in-linux/&#34;&gt;Unix&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&#34;https://windowsloop.com/how-to-add-to-windows-path/&#34;&gt;Windows&lt;/a&gt;) if you wish to reference it via &lt;code&gt;rad&lt;/code&gt;, like in the docs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Verify the rad CLI is installed correctly by running &lt;code&gt;rad version&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Example output:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;RELEASE     VERSION     BICEP       COMMIT
0.26.0      v0.26        0.11.13     2e60bfb46de73ec5cc70485d53e67f8eaa914ba7
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;


      </description>
    </item>
    
